<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-766-149  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 766 149.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  July 19 1989 v138 n47,936 pC7(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Law blocked on using video-display terminal.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gutis, Philip S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Suffolk County New York instituted a law to regulate the use ofvideo-display terminals in 1989, which called for employers to pay80 percent of the cost of an annual eye examination for employeeswho use the terminals and for any needed corrective measures.andP;  Thelaw also mandates periodic breaks and training for workers toavoid health problems.andP;  A court injunction has blocked the eyecare provision, but companies are complying with the trainingprovisions.andP;  Workers' awareness of the potential health problemsof working with VDTs has greatly increased as a result of the law.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ErgonomicsLegal IssuesSuffolk County, New YorkTerminalsHealth Care.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>